        <updateDate>2022-11-30T21:43:49Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>No Surprises for COVID-19 Tests Act</b></p> <p>This bill extends the temporary period during which private health insurance plans must cover testing and related services for COVID-19 without cost sharing. It also temporarily applies certain consumer protections against surprise billing to such testing and related services.</p> <p>Finally, beginning on May 1, 2022, insurance plans without a negotiated price for COVID-19 testing services are no longer required to pay providers the published cash price for such services.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
